================================================================================
Map tiles & geodata (fetched at runtime; attributed in-app)
================================================================================

KP Front renders base maps and reference layers from external tile/data services. These are
NOT redistributed in this repository — they are fetched by the browser or backend-proxied at
runtime, and attributed in the map UI. Operators are responsible for honouring each provider's
terms of use for their deployment.

- swisstopo (geo.admin.ch / wmts.geo.admin.ch) — Swiss federal geodata and geocoding.
    © swisstopo. See https://www.geo.admin.ch/terms-of-use
- OpenStreetMap — © OpenStreetMap contributors, ODbL.
    https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright
- CARTO basemaps (Voyager raster tiles) — © CARTO, built on OpenStreetMap data.
    https://carto.com/attribution
- OpenTopoMap — CC-BY-SA. https://opentopomap.org
- MeteoSwiss (MeteoSchweiz) Open Government Data — current weather observations.
    https://www.meteoswiss.admin.ch
- Open-Meteo — open weather API (forecast fallback). https://open-meteo.com

Per-station reference geodata (hydrants, cantonal WMS, object plans) is NOT part of this
repository; it is loaded into a deployment from a private data source by the operator.

One reference dataset IS bundled: excerpts of the U.S. DOT PHMSA Emergency Response
Guidebook (ERG) 2024 — a public-domain U.S. federal government work — ship as
src/data/erg.json (guide numbers, TIH initial isolation / protective distances), compiled
by tools/gen_erg.py. Provenance and verification notes: tools/erg-source/README.md.

================================================================================
Tactical symbols
================================================================================

The bundled tactical symbol pack (public/tactical-symbols.json) is KP-Front-authored
artwork, generated from geometric primitives by tools/gen_symbols.py and licensed with
the project (AGPL-3.0-or-later). The symbol SHAPES follow the sign conventions of the
Swiss fire-service Faltkarte Einsatzführung published by the Feuerwehr Koordination
Schweiz FKS (feukos.ch), so operators see the signatures they trained on; no third-party
vector artwork is redistributed.

